                            <comment id="14591051" author="yipjustin" created="Thu, 18 Jun 2015 00:55:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yhuai&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yhuai&quot;&gt;yhuai&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14591061" author="marmbrus" created="Thu, 18 Jun 2015 00:58:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve seen this same problem.  I believe the issue is that we no longer cast the date column to a string.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14592617" author="apachespark" created="Thu, 18 Jun 2015 22:02:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;marmbrus&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6888&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6888&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14592654" author="marmbrus" created="Thu, 18 Jun 2015 22:32:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that the fix does also have slight change in semantics from 1.4.0, but I think its worth it to get back support for comparing with partial timestamps.  Now when doing equality comparisons you need to use the rounded timestamp (i.e. &lt;tt&gt;time=&apos;1969-12-31 16:00:00&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;time=&apos;1969-12-31 16:00:00.0&apos;&lt;/tt&gt;).  This does not apply if the users casts manually.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14593915" author="marmbrus" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2015 20:27:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is no longer true as we now special case equality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14594200" author="apachespark" created="Sat, 20 Jun 2015 00:40:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;yhuai&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6914&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6914&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14594214" author="yhuai" created="Sat, 20 Jun 2015 00:51:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Master has been fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6888&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6888&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14594215" author="yhuai" created="Sat, 20 Jun 2015 00:51:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will resolve this one after 1.4 backport is merged.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14595412" author="apachespark" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 06:20:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;navis&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6931&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6931&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14596314" author="yhuai" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 17:45:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 6914&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6914&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6914&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14596316" author="yhuai" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 17:46:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1.4 backport (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6914&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6914&lt;/a&gt;) has been merged.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14596329" author="yhuai" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 17:55:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=marmbrus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;marmbrus&quot;&gt;marmbrus&lt;/a&gt; Do we need to mention it in our release note? If not, I will remove the &lt;tt&gt;releasenotes&lt;/tt&gt; label.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14596395" author="marmbrus" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 18:36:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not anymore, now that we don&apos;t change the equality semantics.  Tag removed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
